==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lowland
<hw>Low"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Land which is low
with respect to the neighboring country; a low or level country; --
opposed to <contr>highland</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The Lowlands</b></col>, <cd>Belgium and Holland; the
Netherlands; also, the southern part of Scotland.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lowlander</ent>⟦br⟧
